Dharamsala and "Little Tibet"

Uprising and the exile of the Dalai Lama - 1959
    - Made his capital Dharamshala, HP, India
    - Issues between Tibetans and local Indians
        - Foreign individuals flood into Dharamsala, because of Tibetans,
          locals are resentful because they are ignored
        - Tibetan look down on local Indians
